Posts.Content: Apr 8, 2015 06:49AM sincitygal702 wrote: Hi Nailsaa I just wanted to say I am sorry that you and your mother are going through this. I am sure it is very worrisome for you and just wanted you to know we are here for you. I hope that your mother gets b9 results, but you should prepare yourself for the worst just in case. A BIRAD 5 is highly suggestive of malignancy. Radiologists are trained professionals who see this kind of stuff everyday, but only a biposy can determine whether or not cancer is present. In the meantime, try to keep your mind busy although I know it is easier said than done! Hopefully you get answers soon, and then can determine what the next steps will be, should there be anything. Please keep us posted. :)
